name: Extra hunny medovik
description:
@Sugartivi | Dear art collector, Russian medovik is made from layers of biscuits, fragrant with caramelised honey, sandwiched between a sweet and rich sour cream filling and coated round with crushed biscuits. It’s quite finicky and time consuming to make. 
There’s also a legend: Once upon a time, a young chef wanted to impress the Empress of the Russian Empire. Not knowing that any dish made with honey drove her mad, he baked a new kind of  cake, flavored with honey, between layers of thick sour cream. It stole her heart and Medovik was born.
